{"author":"Joe Oakhart","author_email":"joeoakhart+bot@navapbc.com","author_id":"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d","data":{"alias":"interfaith-proud-dromedary","description":"# Create canonical AGENTS.md (rebar dev guide) + reduce CLAUDE.md to a thin @AGENTS.md pointer\n\n## Why\n\n`AGENTS.md` is read natively by Codex, Cursor, Copilot's coding agent, Zed, Windsurf, Amp,\nFactory, Jules, Devin, RooCode, and Cline — so a single canonical `AGENTS.md` covers the\necosystem in one move, and Claude Code is bridged by a one-line import. This also fixes the\nsize/duplication anti-pattern: the sections that duplicate `docs/` become one-line pointers.\n\n## What\n\nAuthor a lean `AGENTS.md` at the repo root (target ≤ ~200 lines) that keeps rebar-INTERNAL\ndev specifics inline — Gerrit split-remote workflow, module-size policy, Serena navigation,\nlocal-dev-env, worktree/venv discipline, CI-before-close, signing — and replaces every section\nthat has an authoritative doc with a one-line `docs/…md` pointer (gate protocols →\n`docs/plan-review-gate.md`; MCP tool set → `docs/mcp-reference.md`; quality gates + ticket\ntemplate + project criteria → `docs/plan-review-criteria-guide.md`; store-shares-writes →\n`docs/concurrency.md`; the native topics → the docs created in the re-home story). Then reduce\n`CLAUDE.md` to a `@AGENTS.md` import line plus only genuinely Claude-only notes (if any). Use\nthe mechanism proven by the import spike (fall back to a symlink only if the spike said so).\n\n## Scope\n\nIn: new `AGENTS.md`, rewritten `CLAUDE.md`. Out: `CLAUDE.local.md` (its own story), the\n`.codex`/`.agents` shims and reference sweep (later story), and any code change.\nDepends on: the import spike (mechanism) and the re-home story (docs homes must exist first).\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n\n- [ ] `AGENTS.md` exists at repo root, ≤ ~200 lines, and no section restates a doc that has an\n  authoritative version — each such topic is a one-line pointer.\n  - Proving: `wc -l AGENTS.md` ≤ 200; reviewer confirms pointer-not-duplicate per topic.\n- [ ] rebar-internal dev specifics (Gerrit, module-size, Serena, local-dev-env, worktree/venv,\n  CI-before-close, signing) are present in `AGENTS.md`.\n  - Proving: `rg -c 'Gerrit|module-size|Serena|worktree' AGENTS.md` > 0 for each.\n- [ ] `CLAUDE.md` contains exactly one `@AGENTS.md` import and no duplicated project guidance.\n  - Proving: `rg -c '@AGENTS.md' CLAUDE.md` == 1; `wc -l CLAUDE.md` is small (≤ ~30).\n- [ ] `make lint` passes.","id":"6642-814b-8bc5-4ff4","parent_id":"81e2-ad5e-bfe2-4653","priority":2,"tags":[],"ticket_type":"story","title":"Create canonical AGENTS.md (rebar dev guide) + reduce CLAUDE.md to a thin @AGENTS.md pointer"},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"CREATE","timestamp":1784230954088867001,"uuid":"d871c0f8-12bf-429f-b8af-315fc47eac4a"}